# Cloudflare Plugin — Use Everywhere

VoiceToWebsite runs on **Cloudflare Workers** with **D1**, **KV**, **R2**, **Durable Objects** (BotHubDO, DeployControllerDO, LiveRoomDO, AuditLogDO), and **Workers AI**. For anything related to this stack, use the Cloudflare plugin as the primary source of truth and tooling.

## Documentation (MCP)

- **Before answering** any question about Workers, D1, KV, R2, Durable Objects, wrangler, bindings, AI, or deployment: call **`search_cloudflare_documentation`** (server: `plugin-cloudflare-cloudflare-docs`) with a clear `query` and use the returned docs in your answer.
- Prefer retrieved Cloudflare docs over generic or pre-trained knowledge for API shapes, limits, and best practices.

## When to Use Which Skill / MCP

| Context | Use |
|--------|-----|
| Editing `worker.js`, route handlers, or Worker best practices | **workers-best-practices** skill; `search_cloudflare_documentation` for APIs |
| Editing or adding Durable Objects (`BotHubDO`, `DeployControllerDO`, etc.) | **durable-objects** skill; docs for DO APIs |
| Running or scripting `wrangler` | **wrangler** skill; docs for exact flags |
| Changing `wrangler.toml`, bindings, or env | **cloudflare** skill; **cloudflare-bindings** MCP (D1/KV/R2/Workers tools) when you need to inspect or validate account resources |
| Deploy, build, or tail | **cloudflare-builds** / **cloudflare-observability** MCP when relevant |
| Building an AI agent or MCP server on Workers | **/build-agent** or **/build-mcp** command; **agents-sdk** / **building-mcp-server-on-cloudflare** skills |
| General Cloudflare (Pages, storage, AI, config) | **cloudflare** skill + docs MCP |

## Project Surfaces

- **Worker**: `worker.js` (main), `wrangler.toml` (config, D1/KV/R2/DO/AI bindings).
- **Functions** (called from worker): `functions/*.js` (e.g. `commandCenterApi.js`, `botHub.js`, `execute.js`, `rate-limiter.js`) — they use `env.D1`, `env.KV`, `env.R2`, `env.AI`, and DO stubs.
- **Deploy**: `npm run deploy:live` for the canonical verify -> deploy path; `npm run deploy` is Wrangler-only after verify. Observability lives in `wrangler.toml` (logs, traces).
- **Generated types**: `worker-configuration.d.ts` is generated by `npm run types` (wrangler types). Run it after changing bindings; never hand-write `Env`.

## Config and hygiene (from Cloudflare best practices)

- Keep `compatibility_date` in `wrangler.toml` current (set to today’s date when updating).
- Use `nodejs_compat` (already in use) for Node built-ins.
- Observability: logs and traces are enabled; trace sampling is 0.01 (1%) by default for cost; set to 1 for full traces when debugging.

Use the plugin for everything and anything you possibly can on this project: docs first, then the right skill or MCP (bindings/builds/observability) when it helps.
